highlightText: These two types are  - Structured data - Unstructured data  Let's take a brief look at each  ### Structured Data   _Structured data_ refers to data that can be organised and stored in tables composed of rows and columns  A typical example is data stored in an Excel spreadsheet or a database table containing details about the passengers of an airline company.

highlightText: Direct-Attached Storage (DAS)   Direct-attached storage stands for all types of physical data storage devices you can connect to a _single_ computer/server  Portable and affordable — yet only accessible by one computer at a time — DAS is a standard solution for keeping small-scale records data backups or for transferring data between devices.

#### Data Warehouse Storage - Data warehouses mainly store high-value, structured data that is produced after data transformation operations are completed - The data usually comes from multiple other systems (which could be different company databases) - The processed data is kept in the data warehouse for permanent, long-term storage and to enable analytics - Traditionally, data warehouses were hosted on internal company hardware.

It enables companies to store all of its structured and unstructured data easily and at any scale - One of the most popular data lake tools is Hadoop's distributed file system (HDFS)       - HDFS provides a cost-effective way of storing raw and processed data.

Object storage - Treats each piece of data as a seperate object, keeping in in a seperate storage location and bundles it with related metadata and a unqiue ID to enable easy access and retrieval - One example is Amazon S3, which is ideal for building modern applications that require scale and flexibility.

### Security  - Many cloud providers offer a broad set of policies, technologies, and controls that strengthen overall security  - Cloud companies often rely on robust cybersecurity measures and they hire 3rd party cybersecurity experts to protect sensitive data - Files stored on cloud servers are usually encrypted to help enhance security of the data - Cloud providers rely on firewalls, too, to help protect sensitive files.

- The 2 main types of data being generated and stored are structured (rows and columns) and unstructured (such as text, video and image data) - Traditionally, there were 5 main types of data storage approaches used direct attached storage, network attached storage, storage area networks, software defined storage and hyper-converged storage - To store structured data, the most common types of storage include databases and data warehouse systems.

highlightText: - The main trend nowadays for data storage in industry is to migrate to cloud-based solutions, rather than use on-premise hardware (which is more expensive) - Cloud-based architectures can be public (shared), private (exclusive to a specific company) or a hybrid of both.
